WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.243 --> 00:00:02.983
In the quiet of the desert, inside his tent,

2
00:00:03.029 --> 00:00:04.214
Hamad sits peacefully.

3
00:00:04.570 --> 00:00:07.897
His tent represents his computer, his digital home,

4
00:00:08.097 --> 00:00:10.637
where all his precious files live safely.

5
00:00:11.357 --> 00:00:14.537
Through the golden sky, a saqer soars across the dunes,

6
00:00:14.737 --> 00:00:15.857
a messenger bird,

7
00:00:16.057 --> 00:00:18.432
carrying what appears to be an innocent envelope.

8
00:00:19.486 --> 00:00:22.951
This is email, the modern world's messenger.

9
00:00:24.571 --> 00:00:27.264
The saqer drops the envelope right at Hamad's tent.

10
00:00:28.086 --> 00:00:31.380
Thud, there it sits, seemingly harmless.

11
00:00:31.580 --> 00:00:33.641
Hamad spots the envelope outside his tent. 

12
00:00:33.841 --> 00:00:36.975
He reaches out, picks it up, and examines it.

13
00:00:37.175 --> 00:00:39.657
It looks legitimate, it looks safe. 

14
00:00:39.857 --> 00:00:43.057
This is exactly how computer viruses work.

15
00:00:43.171 --> 00:00:45.635
They disguise themselves as normal files, 

16
00:00:45.835 --> 00:00:49.203
attachments, documents, downloads,

17
00:00:49.403 --> 00:00:52.010
and we open them without a second thought.

18
00:00:53.086 --> 00:00:55.614
Hamad opens the envelope and begins reading.

19
00:00:55.757 --> 00:00:59.089
But while his attention is captured by the letter's contents, 

20
00:00:59.289 --> 00:01:01.243
something sinister is happening,

21
00:01:01.705 --> 00:01:03.969
something he can't see yet.

22
00:01:04.169 --> 00:01:06.680
There, sticking out from inside the envelope,

23
00:01:06.880 --> 00:01:07.924
a virus!

24
00:01:08.124 --> 00:01:12.514
a malicious digital creature that hitched a ride in the attachment.

25
00:01:13.500 --> 00:01:15.289
This is how viruses spread,

26
00:01:15.489 --> 00:01:17.524
hidden inside innocent-looking files,

27
00:01:17.724 --> 00:01:19.344
waiting for the moment you open them,

28
00:01:19.544 --> 00:01:22.367
and once you do, they spring to life.

29
00:01:22.971 --> 00:01:24.891
The virus doesn't waste a second.

30
00:01:24.916 --> 00:01:26.874
It starts multiplying.

31
00:01:27.074 --> 00:01:27.966
One becomes two

32
00:01:28.166 --> 00:01:29.329
two becomes four

33
00:01:29.464 --> 00:01:31.500
four becomes eight.

34
00:01:31.914 --> 00:01:36.492
This is the primary behavior of a computer virus: replication.

35
00:01:37.300 --> 00:01:39.435
They copy themselves over and over, 

36
00:01:39.635 --> 00:01:42.320
spreading through your system like wildfire.

37
00:01:42.714 --> 00:01:44.629
And now, chaos!

38
00:01:44.829 --> 00:01:47.253
The tent is swarming with viruses. 

39
00:01:47.453 --> 00:01:49.557
They are chewing through Hamad's pillows,

40
00:01:49.757 --> 00:01:52.913
his files, corrupting them, destroying them. 

41
00:01:53.113 --> 00:01:54.570
This is what viruses do

42
00:01:54.770 --> 00:01:58.400
They infect your documents, your photos, your programs,

43
00:01:58.600 --> 00:02:00.322
rendering them useless.

44
00:02:00.522 --> 00:02:03.040
Some viruses delete files

45
00:02:03.240 --> 00:02:05.669
others corrupt them beyond repair

46
00:02:05.869 --> 00:02:09.939
and some, they spread to every file they can find.

47
00:02:10.786 --> 00:02:11.846
Hamad panics.

48
00:02:12.046 --> 00:02:14.859
“What’s happening? How do I stop this?”

49
00:02:15.059 --> 00:02:17.589
His peaceful tent has become a nightmare.

50
00:02:17.789 --> 00:02:22.383
Everything he owns is being destroyed right before his eyes.

51
00:02:22.771 --> 00:02:23.928
But wait !

52
00:02:24.128 --> 00:02:26.550
through the chaos, a figure emerges

53
00:02:26.750 --> 00:02:29.589
an old man with a lamp

54
00:02:30.329 --> 00:02:32.796
This is the antivirus

55
00:02:32.996 --> 00:02:35.041
the defender, the protector.

56
00:02:35.241 --> 00:02:37.516
Just as the lamp brings light to darkness, 

57
00:02:37.716 --> 00:02:42.086
antivirus software brings protection to your digital world.

58
00:02:42.286 --> 00:02:44.470
The old man raises his lamp high

59
00:02:44.670 --> 00:02:46.536
and points it directly at the virus.

60
00:02:46.736 --> 00:02:50.764
The light illuminates them, exposing their presence.

61
00:02:50.964 --> 00:02:53.145
This is what antivirus software does

62
00:02:53.345 --> 00:02:54.696
It scans your system,

63
00:02:54.896 --> 00:02:58.632
detecting malicious code that’s hiding in your files.

64
00:02:58.832 --> 00:03:03.116
One by one, the viruses dissolve under the lamp’s light,

65
00:03:03.316 --> 00:03:05.450
gone, eliminated.

66
00:03:05.650 --> 00:03:08.795
The antivirus has successfully removed the threats.

67
00:03:08.995 --> 00:03:10.465
The tent starts to calm.

68
00:03:10.665 --> 00:03:12.275
But look closely

69
00:03:12.475 --> 00:03:16.491
the viruses are gone, but the damage remains.

70
00:03:16.691 --> 00:03:19.909
The pillows are torn, the files are corrupted.

71
00:03:20.109 --> 00:03:23.029
Some things can never be recovered.

